{"questionId":"13107","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( x \\right)\"> <mi>p</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span> is defined by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( x \\right) = {x^3} + 3{x^2} + 8x - 24\"><mi>p</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>24</mn></math></span> where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>∈</mo> <mrow> <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi> </mrow> </math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the remainder when <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is divided by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {x - 2} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\\left( 2 \\right) = 8 - 12 + 16 - 24\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>8</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>12</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>16</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>24</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for a valid attempt at remainder theorem or polynomial division.</p>\n<p>=&nbsp;−12&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>remainder&nbsp;=&nbsp;−12</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13107","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_10a.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the remainder when p ( x ) is divided by ( x − 2 ) .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.17—Poisson distribution","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.8—Transformations of graphs, composite transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}